OMMUNIST BLOC\n\nCommunist China - India: Peiping has again raised with New Delhi the subject of a civil air agreement. At present, Burma is the only nonbloc Asian nation with which Communist China has an air agreement. New Delhi has just signed an air agreement with the USSR, and may accede to Peiping's request. (Page 1)\n\nUSSR - Latin America: The highest ranking delegations from the USSR and the Eastern European satellites to visit Latin America in recent years will attend the inauguration of Argentine President-elect Frondizi on 1 May. The Soviet delegation will include First Deputy Foreign Minister Kuznetsov, who will also visit Mexico briefly. The bloc representation will include Rumania, Poland, Czechoslovakia, Hungary, and Bulgaria, and will add impetus to the bloc's intensified efforts to increase trade and diplomatic relations with Latin America.\n\nII. ASIA-AFRICA\n\nIndonesia: establishing \"amphibious Task Force 17\" is the first positive evidence to substantiate earlier reports of an impending attack on the west coast of Sumatra. the task force is under the command of Lt. Col. John Lie, captain of the navy's flagship, the destroyer Gadja Mada, and indicates that naval units are, as previously reported, actually on station off Padang. The assault, originally scheduled for 15", "token_count": 202, "token_end_0based": 210, "token_start_0based": 9, "token_text": "the communist bloc communist china india peiping has again raised with new delhi the subject of a civil air agreement at present burma is the only nonbloc asian nation with which communist china has an air agreement new delhi has just signed an air agreement with the ussr and may accede to peiping's request page 1 ussr latin america the highest ranking delegations from the ussr and the eastern european satellites to visit latin america in recent years will attend the inauguration of argentine president-elect frondizi on 1 may the soviet delegation will include first deputy foreign minister kuznetsov who will also visit mexico briefly the bloc representation will include rumania poland czechoslovakia hungary and bulgaria and will add impetus to the bloc's intensified efforts to increase trade and diplomatic relations with latin america ii asia-africa indonesia establishing amphibious task force 17 is the first positive evidence to substantiate earlier reports of an impending attack on the west coast of sumatra the task force is under the command of lt col john lie captain of the navy's flagship the destroyer gadja mada and indicates that naval units are as previously reported actually on station off padang the assault originally scheduled for 15", "unred_source_page": 4}
