nsidering Civil Air Agreement With Communist China\n\nIndian Prime Minister Nehru is again considering the advisability of concluding a civil air agreement with Communist China. the Chinese have complained to Nehru that India's recent air agreement with the USSR and New Delhi's favoritism toward air services to Europe have \"slighted\" Peiping.\n\nOfficials of the government-controlled Indian international airline seem to feel that air service to China would be uneconomical and that the two new Super-Constellations soon to be delivered to India will be required on the Soviet route. Economic objections raised by India", "token_count": 99, "token_end_0based": 98, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "i the communist bloc india again considering civil air agreement with communist china indian prime minister nehru is again considering the advisability of concluding a civil air agreement with communist china the chinese have complained to nehru that india's recent air agreement with the ussr and new delhi's favoritism toward air services to europe have slighted peiping officials of the government-controlled indian international airline seem to feel that air service to china would be uneconomical and that the two new super-constellations soon to be delivered to india will be required on the soviet route economic objections raised by india", "unred_source_page": 7}
